     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <hr> 
     <h3>What is <em>Classroom to Congregation</em>?</h3> 
     <p><em>Classroom to Congregation</em> offers the resources of the Westmont faculty <strong><img src="images/classroom-shot.jpg" alt="classroom" width="302" height="201"></strong> to meet the educational needs of local congregations. By offering a wide variety of presentation topics, the Westmont faculty are eager to help your community think through the intersection of faith with contemporary moral issues and lifelong enduring questions. </p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p><strong>How does <em>Classroom to </em><em> Congregation</em> work?</strong></p> 
     <p>There are many ways to participate in <em>Classroom to Congregation</em>. Simply click on the "Topics" link to find the different prepared faculty presentations. When you click on a specific topic it will take you to the bio of the presenting faculty member. If there is a particular faculty member that you are familiar with you can search for them under the "Faculty Bios" link. Once you have decided on a topic(s), please fill out our form, found under "Speaking Inquiries".</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p>If you do not see a topic that fits the needs of your congregation, we are happy to discuss the topic and help to connect you with a faculty member who might be wiling create a presentation(s) that will meet the goals and purpose of the desired program. If you want to suggest a topic not listed, please complete the first and third sections of the form and indicate the desired topic in the provided "Questions and Comments" box.</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p><strong>How much does <em>Classroom to Congregation</em> cost?</strong></p> 
     <p>We do not want cost to keep you from taking advantage of this opportunity. However, it is important to compensate the faculty members for their time and energies. A standard honorarium is $75 per speaker/per occasion.</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p>We are more than willing to work with each church/organization if the cost is a problem. On the"Speaking Inquiries" form there is a space where you can request a scholarship to help bring a faculty presentation to your congregation.</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
     <p><strong>Questions?</strong></p> 
     <p>If you have specific questions, please feel free to fill out the "Speaking Inquiries", or email us at <a href="mailto:libarts@westmont.edu">libarts@westmont.edu</a>. We look forward to working with you!</p> 
     <p>&nbsp;</p> 
